President Barack Obama issued a statement on Chairman John Dingell, who became the longest-serving member in the history of the United States House of Representatives. President Obama commended Chairman Dingell for his service and thanked him for his contributions. He highlighted Dingell's advocacy for the health and well-being of Americans, including his efforts to provide national health insurance and his instrumental role in the passage of the 1965 Medicare Act. Dingell's work in protecting the environment, improving water quality, promoting renewable energy, and addressing toxic waste was also acknowledged. President Obama praised Dingell's commitment to fiscal responsibility and government transparency, particularly his investigations into waste, fraud, and abuse. He expressed gratitude on behalf of the American people and looked forward to working with Dingell in the future.